[[{"text": ["If you are trying to automate some task in a website you might want to look at WWW::Selenium.", "It, along with Selenium Remote Control, allows you to remote control a web browser."], "childNum": 3, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "WWW::Selenium", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [{"text": "WWW::Selenium", "tag": "code"}], "childNum": 1, "href": "http://search.cpan.org/dist/Test-WWW-Selenium/lib/WWW/Selenium.pm"}, {"text": "WWW::Selenium", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": -1, "childList": []}, {"text": "Selenium Remote Control", "tag": "a", "pos": 1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://seleniumhq.org/projects/remote-control/"}]}], [{"text": ["In Python there is ctypes and in Perl there is Win32::API"], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "ctypes", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://www.python.org/doc/2.5.2/lib/module-ctypes.html"}, {"href": "http://search.cpan.org/~cosimo/Win32-API-0.58/API.pm", "text": "Win32::API", "childNum": 0, "tag": "a", "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["ctypes Example"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": [{"text": "ctypes Example", "childNum": 0, "tag": "strong", "pos": 0, "childList": []}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n from ctypes import *\nwindll.user32.MessageBoxA(None, \"Hey MessageBox\", \"ctypes\", 0);\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 2}, {"text": ["Win32::Api Example"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 3, "childList": [{"text": "Win32::Api Example", "childNum": 0, "tag": "strong", "pos": 0, "childList": []}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n use Win32::GUI qw( WM_CLOSE );\nmy $tray = Win32::GUI::FindWindow(\"WindowISearchFor\",\"WindowISearchFor\");\nWin32::GUI::SendMessage($tray,WM_CLOSE,0,0);\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 4}], [{"text": ["To answer the actual question, in Perl, you would use the SendMouse (and the associated functions) provided by the Win32::GuiTest module."], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "Win32::GuiTest", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://search.cpan.org/~karasik/Win32-GuiTest-1.56/"}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n #!/usr/bin/perl\n\nuse strict;\nuse warnings;\n\nuse Win32::GuiTest qw( MouseMoveAbsPix SendMouse );\n\nMouseMoveAbsPix(640,400);\nSendMouse \"{LEFTCLICK}\";\n\n__END__\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 1}, {"text": ["UPDATE:"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 2, "childList": [{"text": "UPDATE:", "childNum": 0, "tag": "strong", "pos": 0, "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["In that case, you would use FindWindowLike to find the window and MouseClick to send a click to that specific window."], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 3, "childList": [{"text": "FindWindowLike", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}, {"text": "MouseClick", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "childList": []}]}], [{"text": ["See this:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": []}, {"text": ["http://xkcd.com/196/"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": [{"text": "http://xkcd.com/196/", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://xkcd.com/196/"}]}], [{"text": ["If using a different tool is allowed, you should take a look at AutoHotkey or AutoIt.", "These tools were made for this sort of thing, and I've always been keen on using the right tools for the right jobs."], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "AutoHotkey", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://www.autohotkey.com/"}, {"text": "AutoIt", "tag": "a", "pos": -1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://www.autoitscript.com/autoit3/"}]}, {"text": ["AutoHotkey is based on AutoIt I believe, and it is my personal preference.", "You only really need 2 functions for what you're trying to achieve, MouseMove and MouseClick."], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": [{"text": "MouseMove", "tag": "a", "pos": 1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://www.autohotkey.com/docs/commands/MouseMove.htm"}, {"href": "http://www.autohotkey.com/docs/commands/MouseClick.htm", "text": "MouseClick", "childNum": 0, "tag": "a", "childList": []}]}], [{"text": ["I find this is easier to approach in Java or C++.", "Java has a Robot class that allows you to just pass x, y coordinates and click somewhere.", "Using C++, you can achieve that same functionality using mouse_event() or SendMessage() with the WM_MOUSE_DOWN flag.", "SendMessage is more technical but it allows you to use FindWindow() and send mouse clicks to a specific window, even if it's minimized."], "childNum": 5, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "Robot class", "tag": "a", "pos": 1, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.2/docs/api/java/awt/Robot.html"}, {"text": "mouse_event()", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 2, "childList": []}, {"text": "SendMessage()", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": -1, "childList": []}, {"text": "WM_MOUSE_DOWN", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": -1, "childList": []}, {"text": "FindWindow()", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 3, "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["Using a scripting language like Python or Ruby, I'd guess that you'd end up hooking into one of these Windows API functions anyway."], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": []}]]